Wrap quality statistic of identity r regression.

Source: R/FTest.R
wrapFTest.lm.Rd

Wrap quality statistic of identity r regression.

# S3 method for lm
wrapFTest(x, ..., format = NULL)

Arguments

x

lm model
...

extra arguments (not used)
format

if set the format to return ("html", "latex", "markdown", "ascii", "docx", ...)

Value

formatted string

Examples


d <- data.frame(x=c(1,2,3,4,5,6,7,7),
                y=c(1,1,2,2,3,3,4,4))
model <- lm(y~x,data=d)
summary(model)

#>

#>

#> x            0.51568    0.04622  11.156 3.09e-05 ***
#> ---
#> Signif. codes:  0 ‘***’ 0.001 ‘**’ 0.01 ‘*’ 0.05 ‘.’ 0.1 ‘ ’ 1
#> 
#> Residual standard error: 0.2769 on 6 degrees of freedom
#> Multiple R-squared:  0.954,	Adjusted R-squared:  0.9463 
#> F-statistic: 124.5 on 1 and 6 DF,  p-value: 3.094e-05
#> 
sigr::wrapFTest(model)

#> [1] "F Test summary: (R2=0.954, F(1,6)=124.5, p=3.094e-05)."
